https://podman.io/docs/installation#ubuntu

I have used ubuntu multipass here:-
Nomad Version: 1.9.13+ent
Podman version: 4.9.3
Noamd Client machine OS : Linux nomad-client 6.8.0-88-generic #89-Ubuntu SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Sat Oct 11 00:59:18 UTC 2025 aarch64 aarch64 aarch64 GNU/Linux
 
-- Install podman on Nomad client node --  Reference https://podman.io/docs/installation#ubuntu
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install podman
podman --version
 
####### Install nomad-driver-podman on Nomad client node ###### Reference https://developer.hashicorp.com/nomad/plugins/drivers/podman#installation
 
Install the required packages.
$ sudo apt-get update && \
  sudo apt-get install wget gpg coreutils
Add the HashiCorp [GPG key][gpg-key].
$ wget -O- https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg
Add the official HashiCorp Linux test repository.
$ echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list
Update and install.
$ sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y nomad-driver-podman
 
 
####### nomad-server.hcl ######
data_dir  = "/opt/nomad/data"
bind_addr = "0.0.0.0"

server {
  license_path = "/etc/nomad.d/license.hclic"
  enabled          = true
  bootstrap_expect = 1
}
 
######## nomad-client.hcl ########
data_dir  = "/opt/nomad/data"
bind_addr = "0.0.0.0"

client {
  enabled          = true
  server_join {
  retry_join = [ "<nomad-server-ip>" ]
}
}

plugin_dir = "/opt/nomad/plugins"

plugin "nomad-driver-podman" {
  config {
      socket_path = "unix:///run/podman/podman.sock"
      # Customize other Podman driver plugin options here if needed
  }
}
 
Note: Copy /usr/bin/nomad-driver-podman binary to /opt/nomad/plugins on Nomad client node and then start the nomad.
 
######## job.hcl #############
job "nginx-podman-job" {
  datacenters = ["dc1"]
  type = "service"

  group "nginx-group" {
    count = 1

    task "nginx-task" {
      driver = "podman"

      config {
        image = "docker.io/library/nginx:latest"
      }

      resources {
        cpu = 500
        memory = 256
      }
    }
  }
}
 
nomad job run job.hcl
